## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the CodeJudge project.

### Changes Made

#### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in `package.json`
- `package-lock.json` updated with new dependency tree

#### 2. Analytics Component Integration
Modified `app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag, after all other content
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics Quickstart guide (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):

1. **Framework Detection**: Identified this as a Next.js project using the App Router (based on app/ directory structure)
2. **Package Manager**: Using npm (identified by presence of package-lock.json)
3. **Integration Point**: Added Analytics component to the root layout (`app/layout.tsx`) inside the body tag
4. **Placement**: Component placed after all application content to ensure it doesn't interfere with rendering

### Build Verification

- TypeScript compilation: ✓ Successful
- The full build encountered pre-existing Supabase environment variable issues unrelated to this change
- No new linting errors introduced by Analytics integration

### Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard under Analytics section
2. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy`
3. Verify tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after deployment

### Files Modified

- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency resolution
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
